      bearCase: "Geopolitical tensions could escalate, leading to a broader risk-off environment that negatively impacts speculative assets. Regulatory hurdles, as seen in New Hampshire, could slow institutional adoption and create uncertainty. A reversal in the dollar\'s weakness or a correction in the tech sector could remove key external catalysts for Bitcoin\'s price.",
      neutralCase: "Bitcoin\'s price may stabilize around current levels, fluctuating in response to a mix of macroeconomic signals and minor crypto-specific developments. DeFi may continue its gradual re-rating, but overall market sentiment could remain cautious due to persistent regulatory ambiguity and global economic uncertainties.",
      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "Medium-term outlook is cautiously optimistic (60% probability of continued upward momentum with volatility) for Bitcoin, driven by macro factors. DeFi has a higher probability (70%) of continued relative outperformance within the crypto sector, assuming no major security breaches or regulatory crackdowns. Regulatory integration at the state level faces significant headwinds (20% probability of near-term success).",
